comments.message:
It is important to note that the current implementation works for only Intel. I would suggest considering the addition of fan inventory information similar to what has been done for other components such as PowerSupply and fabric_adapters.

When incorporating fan inventory add sensors and cooled_by association to Fan Inventory. Here is an example:

For sensors:
{
    "types": {
        "rType": "inventory",
        "fType": "sensors"
    },
    "paths": [
        "/xyz/openbmc_project/sensors/fan_tach/fan1_0",  // sensor paths
        "/xyz/openbmc_project/sensors/fan_tach/fan1_1"
    ]
}

For cooled_by association:
{
    "types": {
        "rType": "cooled_by",
        "fType": "cooling"
    },
    "paths": [
        "/xyz/openbmc_project/inventory/system/chassis"  // Chassis path
    ]
}

we typically don't use the ternary operator in bmcweb. 
I think you already have a default of "Enabled" in case this interface doesn't exist on D-Bus... so not sure why this can't just be

if (!value) { aResp->res.jsonValue["Status"]["State"] = "Absent"; }
